Global Lead Battery Recycling Market Insights
Lead Battery Recycling Market size was valued at USD 16.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 24.0 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.0% from 2024 to 2030.

Lead Battery Recycling Market Overview
The global Lead Battery Recycling market was valued at USD 18.5 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 25.3 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 5.1% during the forecast period. This growth is primarily driven by the increasing demand for lead-acid batteries in various sectors, including automotive and industrial applications, alongside the rising focus on sustainability and resource recovery. Lead battery recycling plays a crucial role in the circular economy by reducing the environmental impact of lead production and promoting resource efficiency.

